From 5063b184adbec81da864625370a1ad8c02815d31 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Benjamin Larsson <banan@ludd.ltu.se>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 16:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 15/16] net: airoha: en7523: fix GDM3 hw-NAT egress queue
 (NBQ=6)

Hardware NAT offload through the EN7523 GDM3 port (the USB/XSI HSGMII
serdes LAN port, e650 "lan4") blackholed every offloaded frame while
GDM1/GDM2 worked and software forwarding through GDM3 was fine.

Comparing the FOE entry built by this driver against the one the vendor
firmware programs for the same flow (via hw_nat -g) shows the egress
info-block-2 differs only in the destination queue:

  vendor  downlink (->GDM3): INFO2=0x266  PSE_PORT=3, PSE_QOS, NBQ=6
  mainline downlink (->GDM3): INFO2=0x260  PSE_PORT=3, PSE_QOS, NBQ=0

GDM3 is the USB serdes port, whose source-port queue is nbq 6 (the same
value the RX source-port path maps to HSGMII_LAN_7523_USB_SRCPORT). With
NBQ=0 the PPE targets a PSE port-3 queue that the USB-serdes output never
services, so the frame is dropped. The driver only set IB2_NBQ for DSA
ports, leaving GDM3 at 0.

Set IB2_NBQ=6 for EN7523 GDM3 egress. The vendor offloads this path at
942 Mbit/s; with this fix the mainline driver hardware-forwards GDM3
flows instead of blackholing them.

Signed-off-by: Benjamin Larsson <banan@ludd.ltu.se>
Signed-off-by: Matheus Sampaio Queiroga <srherobrine20@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c
index 06d81bc62..b33ecf90e 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c
@@ -612,6 +612,17 @@ static int airoha_ppe_foe_entry_prepare(struct airoha_eth *eth,
 			if (dsa_port >= 0)
 				val |= FIELD_PREP(AIROHA_FOE_IB2_NBQ,
 						  dsa_port);
+			else if (airoha_is(eth, en7523) &&
+				 port->id == AIROHA_GDM3_IDX)
+				/* GDM3 (USB serdes) hw-NAT egress needs the USB
+				 * source-port queue (nbq 6, the same value used on
+				 * the RX source-port path). The vendor FOE uses
+				 * INFO2=0x266 (PSE_PORT=3, PSE_QOS, NBQ=6); with
+				 * NBQ=0 the frame targets a PSE port-3 queue the
+				 * USB-serdes output never services, so hw-forwarded
+				 * GDM3 traffic is blackholed.
+				 */
+				val |= FIELD_PREP(AIROHA_FOE_IB2_NBQ, 6);
 
 			smac_id = port->id;
 		}
